Rail
JR West and Ichibata Electric Railway serves the prefecture in terms of rail transportation .
The Sanin Main Line goes through the prefecture on the Sea of Japan side going into major cities such as Matsue and Izumo .
and stations are the major stops in the prefecture .
The Kisuki line , which forks from Shinji Station on the Sanin Line , connects with the Geibi Line in Hiroshima Prefecture , cutting into the Chūgoku Mountains .
Ichibata Electric Railway serve the Shimane peninsula from Dentetsu-Izumoshi Station and Izumo Taisha-Mae Station to Matsue Shinjiko-Onsen Station .
JR West has 3 Limited Express trains to Shimane , which are Super Matsukaze , Super Oki , and Yakumo .
