Economy
In Shimane , the largest employer is the retailing industry , employing over 60,000 workers .
Mishimaya and Juntendo are examples of companies .
The manufacturing industry has the second number of employees with 49,000 workers .
In the number of business locations , the retailing industry is first with over 12,000 .
Twenty-nine percent of the total industry income is from the service industry , including retailers .
Another 13 % is from the manufacturing industry .
